name: Sunny Szpak-Holly
bio: Winnipeg based photographer capturing family milestones from maternity to newborn and beyond. Sunny S-H Photography studio is located in St Boniface.

social_posts.post_text: Miss Maddie stole my cold black heart this past weekend.  This image makes me smile and laugh.  Just what we all need on a cold miserable day in #winnipeg.  Fun fact.  Her mama is the owner of @crankedenergy  An amazing local business that I just happen to have several cases of in my freezer.
When you are born with an Epic name like Link, you deserve an epic first photoshoot.  I think the Legend of Zelda fans will appreciate mom and dads attention to detail for props.
Jackson just turned one!  Due to food allergy concerns we opted to do a paint smash today. He is just one of the sweetest babies I’ve met.
Quinn is turning 3!  I love any excuse to catch up with this guy and his parents.

I cannot thank @dawn_mcewen and @aceburpee enough for volunteering today for my Santa Paws event. $2200+ was raised for @mgprescue.  Also a huge thank you to @mcconl3 who baked up a storm (while super pregnant). Watch for your photos coming by email in the next couple days.  This annual event is one of my faves.

Thank you to @aceburpee and @dawn_mcewen for being such great guest Santa’s for this years fundraiser that raise over $2200 for @mgprescue and thank you to all who came out and also baked goods for the event.  See you again next year!!! #santapaws #winnipegpetphotographer #winnipegdogphotography #

Meet 1 month old Jaylen.  Yes “older” newborn sessions are more challenging, but having images like this are priceless.  And shout out to @ryandpdesign for this crazy soft bamboo sleeper.  I got a few sizes of this one for the studio.

This years top 9 most “liked” images on my page are kinda unexpected. (How’s to show how much marketing on IG has changed). No shock that @anroup and her surrogacy journey was so loved.  Photos of me though??? @ianmcc  gets the credit for those :). Oh and shout out to @minimalist.mother.inthe.making and her wild birth session.

Ummmm. Just wow.  This gorgeous couture gown arrived this week just in time for @annejosie and both of them could not be more perfect.  We created some fun new content for her website and I’m pumped for her second maternity session with the family. (Gown is available as part of my studio closet for client use).
A little behind the scenes before and after of yesterdays magical maternity with @annejosie #maternitygown #maternityphotography #winnipegmaternityphotographer
11 day old little miracle Clara and her loving fur brother Ari.  These two are going to be best friends.
Twins are always double the fun!!! Happy upcoming first birthday Lily and Ella.  It was such a pleasure to meet you.
Today I had the pleasure of meeting almost one year old Aurora-Wynter.  This setup was moms request to celebrate her Nunavut roots.
Miss Audrey was also in the studio today for a swaddled newborn.  She is 7 weeks old today, super alert and just content as can be.  And that hair!!!!
I can’t believe Austin is about to turn one.  It’s been so much fun watching this family over the past year.  From maternity, newborn, Christmas mini to smash.
I love that this expectant mom chose only silks for her maternity session.  It’s literally impossible to get the same image twice with the movement and light.
Such a perfect palette for the Winnipeg weather.  Meet 13 day old Madison.
Last shoot before Christmas and I couldn’t ask for a cuter subject.  Christopher is celebrating his first birthday Christmas Eve and his first winter in Winnipeg!
So many new moms I meet regret not capturing this part of your families story.  It’s my job to show you just how gorgeous you are (and have fun doing it).

My last newborn shoot for 2022 and we are going out with a bang.  My incredible friend @mcconl3 delivered this perfect human via surrogacy.  9 day old Marceau’s dads are from France and England but currently living in Amsterdam. And the egg donor is from Ontario.  He has already had quite the adventure and it’s only begun.

Here we go!  My newborns of 2022.  This has become one of my favorite traditions every year.  Thank you to everyone single family who chose me to capture their tiny humans first moments.  It truly is an honor that I do not take lightly.  Cheers to a great year and to all the babies coming to the studio next year :)
7 month old Carter was in for his sitting stage session today.  He didn’t quite get the memo about not crawling yet and was super busy and full of smiles.

Let’s cap off 2022 with the session I did for 9 year old Chilly Dog.  His human surprised the family with portraits of him and I couldn’t think of a better Christmas present.  And just look at that smile.
The journey that had to happen to welcome 9 day old Marceau involved science, surrogacy, love, losses and determination. He is truly a little miracle rainbow baby.
Could not think of a better way to start off the new year in the studio than this.  36 weeks and just glowing. (Gown is a new edition to the studio closet).
First newborn in the studio for the year and she was simply perfect.  We just “hung out” for a while ;)

This show stopping gown is now part of my studio closet.  All available gowns are in a gallery accessible on my website anytime.  There is no reason to buy anything for your maternity shoot.  I got ya covered.  Literally.
Miss Adrienne was super serious about cake time.  I get it. It’s a serious situation.
Ava and Mia are just about to turn one.  You can see their personalities in the two smashes.

Introducing the “Wednesday litter” available for adoption from @mgprescue.  These sweeties are only 7 weeks old.  If you are looking for a forever furry friend, please contact the rescue.  So many amazing dogs are in need of homes.  Thank you @radjill for wrangling.

37 weeks and about to welcome baby number 4.  I LOVE that more expectant moms are choosing to capture and celebrate pregnancy.  My goal is always to make each mom see just how gorgeous they are and have fun doing it.

My second maternity session for the day was for this stunning mama who’s 32 weeks along.  I put dad to work tossing fabric and he may have been my most enthusiastic assistant.  Maybe I should hire him.  Just look at that movement.

It’s nerve wracking for most expectant mamas to come in and be the focus of a maternity session.  But watching the confidence grow through out the shoot and trusting the process is my favorite part.  Todays gorgeous client not only has an adorable bump, but she brought her super supportive partner and big lug of a rottie to the session.  So yeah, we had fun!  Bring on the upcoming baby boom :)
Leo is turning one and today we celebrated!  This guy was “talking” up a storm and is so full of personality already.
Double the fun!!
This little miracle, who arrived into the world via surrogacy is on the blog.  Go check it out.
This handsome guy came all the way from Neepawa today to celebrate his upcoming first birthday.  Happy birthday Cyrus.

Had the best time with them 🥰 

#behindthescenesphotoshoot #healthypregnancy #maternityphotography #familyphotoshoots #winnipegphotography #maternity #familygoals #familyphotoshoot #pregnancyfashion #pregnancyphotoshoot #pregnancyphotography #enceinte #photographiegrossesse #grossesseheureuse #grossessehealthy #maternité
32 weeks and so ready to meet baby number two.  Not only will I be photographing this newborn, but I will be capturing the birth as well!
Wishing Chase the happiest of first birthdays today.  So honored to have spent time celebrating your big day with you. And yes he loved the cake.
#nordicdynamite taking some sweet jumps like a pro (because he basically is).
Don’t forget the 6-8 month baby sitting stage milestone.  Probably my fave stage when they sit, smile and have all the rolls.  7 month old Carter’s session just hit the blog.
Don’t miss out on capturing those tiny newborn details.  Book your 2023 session and secure your spot.
Okay.  I had a little bit of editing fun on this image shot simply on red.  Is it over the top?  Yep.  But do we love it? (Digital backdrop composite).

6 year old Atticus was in the studio for a portrait session.  At the end of the month he will have surgery to remove one eye.  The good news is soon he will be pain free and living his best life with a super wicked wink ;)
2 week old Artemis.  Her dad is leaving this weekend to serve overseas so I wanted him to have this image right away.
Quite possibly the best maternity session out take ever.  #downwardfacingdog #fitpregnancy

I’m just loving all the baby bumps in the studio lately. Love that families and mamas want to capture this milestone.  Did you know I provide all the gowns?  I have over 40 in my studio closet to make your session simply amazing.  This bump just hit the blog. Go check it out.
9 day old Amiko.  Don’t let this photo fool you.  She was one of the most aware/alert babies in a long time.  You will see more from her session soon as she was my model for a promo video :)
Snug as a bug. (In a purple rug)
22 day old Prataap was in today for a swaddled newborn session.  This option is perfect for more alert newborns and those who just want a few gorgeous images.
Cake smashes are not just about making a mess.  We also clean up :)
Mr Aiden turned one yesterday!  Today was his first big photoshoot and he was so excited we had to contain him :)
Some previews from todays studio valentine minis.  Next round of minis will be mom and me minis (around Mother’s Day).
Sometimes simple is best.  12 day old Cameron agrees.  I didn’t even see his eyes today.  He slept through the whole thing.
#dogscatchingtreats is something I’ve wanted to do for a while. And my girl Sophie never misses.
38 weeks and simply stunning.  I cannot wait to meet this baby very soon!
Some kids don’t like to make a mess.  1 year old Wally on the other hand…
14 day old Sarina with her moms wedding sari.
Simple is often my favorite.

Sweet 7 month old Noa was adopted through @mgprescue not long ago and her new family booked a portrait session for her.  Because she’s recovering from a broken leg (that she came into care with) we did the session outdoors and clearly it was the best decision. She’s glowing!!! So happy to see this girl healthy and thriving.
Sharing is caring!  Liam was in today to celebrate his first birthday and of course I encouraged his big brother to join in.  He said it was the best day ever.

Behind the scenes and a few final images from a recent newborn session in studio.  Props, wraps, backdrops and anything baby may need is provided and on hand to make the whole experience stress free for everyone.  With over 13 years experience, my goal is to create priceless images in a safe and welcoming studio environment. #winnipegnewbornphotographer #winnipegnewbornphotography 📷 @gabrielletouchettephoto
Yes Nola.  That’s how I look at cake too.
Miss Azalea is turning one.  She was a tough nut to crack but as long as she was continuously fed she allowed the shoot to happen.
This magical gown is now part of my studio closet available for client use.  You will see more behind the scenes soon thanks to @gabrielletouchettephoto :)
Over 5 years ago I did my very first shoot with @mgprescue and the snowmobile litter.  How lucky am I that Viper came in for a portrait session today.  His eyes have barely changed.
Every single parent knows just how fast babies grow.  How every day they change.  Newborn photography captures the details, how curly they are, how perfect they are. 📷 @gabrielletouchettephoto
Miss Rhaegan turns 4 months old tomorrow and came to see me all the way from Ontario.  Her giggles made my day.

Todays studio shoot was fun!!! 11 year old Jayde has retired from competitive gymnastics and wanted a photoshoot to celebrate her accomplishments.  I’m in awe of just how strong and disciplined she is.
Today was a wild day with three studio maternity sessions.  First up is this stunner.  She came prepared with her own glam squad (which is awesome!!!).
I just love this one.  The real smiles.  The closeness.  Soon they will be a family of three.
When your humans get you your very own little human best friend.  8 day old Maeve.
Sweet 3 week old Anastasia.  Sometimes either mom or baby need some extra time before coming to the studio for medical reasons.  That is okay!  Safety and health always come first.
Such a pleasure to meet 10 day old Wemberly all the way from Gillam, MB.  She really tried to stay awake.  Tried so hard.  But she failed.

Tried to make a reel but it was not showing half the dogs.  But here are the amazing pups who took part in Sundays pet portrait fundraiser in support of @mgprescue and @kismetcreekfarm  Thank you to all who came out and supported.
Just sent out this incredible young ladies gallery.  So much power, strength and discipline.
Miss Presley was in the studio today to celebrate turning one.  This was her first taste of sweets.  Seems she approves.
I made a new friend today. She’s 2 and she’s adorable.  Also she’s going to be a big sister soon :)
Symmetry and lighting are my favorite!!! So happy I was given the opportunity to photograph @jaydeflips and for her willingness to play along.
Sweet 19 day old Sara was in the studio today for a swaddled newborn session.  We got a perfect mix of alert and sleepy shots.
Todays maternity session was simply perfect.  She’s 38 weeks and I cannot wait to meet baby soon!!!
12 day old Amara says “smile it’s Friday”.
Vivienne is turning one and today we celebrated.  She tried to show restraint but the delicious cake was too much to resist.
First of two studio maternity sessions.  This silk fabric is just magical.  It’s shows all the curves.  It reminds me of a waterfall.
Soon they will be a family of four!  And miss A is very excited :)

Behind the scenes of a studio maternity portrait session.  Moms have a studio closet of over 50 looks to choose from to create and capture stunning images that will be cherished for generations to come. #winnipegmaternityphotographer #winnipegmaternityphotography #manitobamaternityphotographer #fineartmaternity #maternityphotography #maternityshoot #winnipegphotographer
That excitement when your humans get you your own tiny human. (15 day old Remy).
12 day old Julian.  His parents are over the moon in love with this little guy.
10 day old Everett has completed their family and I’m pretty sure they are all smitten with him.
Happy first birthday Nova.  And thank you for coming to see me today.
7 month old Atlas was in the studio today for an absolutely adorable sitter stage session.

How do you pose a litter of 12 week old pyrs?  You don’t. You wait till they are ready.  Thank you do the amazing fosters and helpers who came out today.  These babies will be looking for forever families soon :) @mgprescue @radjill @mcconl3
When your friends get a puppy and you get to do baby photos they day they pick her up.  Happy gotcha day 8 week old Belle.
10 day old Kieran came to see me today.  He was such a sweetie and slept through most of the visit.
This gorgeous client is about to be a mama of four!

On Monday, March 13, miss Anastasia entered the world completely as her mom planned.  It was in their home, peaceful, unassisted, and simply incredible.  The midwife was there to make sure mom and baby where safe, but mom did it her way with her husband (and dog) by her side.  This was unlike any birth I’ve witnessed and it was truly an honor to be there to capture it.  AJ you are a warrior.
Just me over here crushing on all these gorgeous maternity shoots lately.  Today I got to see this mama again.  Soon she will be holding baby number three :)

7 week old Gunner.  His humans saw photos I had done last week of Belle (from the same breeder) and reached out to get baby photos of their new family member.  Of course I said yes.  This handsome guy is gonna be a big boy!!!!
14 day old Kacper came to visit me today.  His mom warned me he was grumpy today.  He didn’t make a peep the whole shoot :)

A few more images from the home birth I had the honor of capturing last week.  Baby Anastasia is already a week old!  I can’t wait to see her for her home newborn session end of the month. (The first image just makes me smile). #homebirth #birthphotography #winnipegphotographer #naturalbirth #naturalbirthing #winnipegfamilyphotographer #winnipegnewbornphotographer

Happy 3rd birthday Enzo.  Thank you for spending part of your special day with me.

9 years ago, at my very first rescue shoot ever, I met my dog crush Lula and her brother Rocky.  Lula seemed to take forever to find her forever family.  Be she was just waiting for the perfect humans, and she got them. Oh, and they later adopted her brother when he came back into rescue care.  I’ve been so lucky to keep contact with her humans and I have photographed her countless times.  Sadly, with a recent diagnosis her humans reached out to do a #projectgooddog session.  A lifetime is just never enough.  I’m just happy she had 9 of the best years possible and I know they will cherish any more time they get with her. She will forever be my #dogcrush .
Caption this.
Pretty sure this is the face I make eating cake too.  Happy upcoming first birthday Ayla.  You are just the sweetest little lady.
This mama, this gown, this backdrop.  Just perfect.  Soon she will be holding her little one. (New gown part of my studio closet for client use).

17 days ago, I had the honor of capturing Anastasia’s home birth.  It only seemed fitting to do her newborn session at home with all of the mayhem that comes with family, dog and toddler life.  This whole journey has been incredible to witness and I’m still in awe of mom.  I have to admit, it was kinda fun to dust off my “on location” lifestyle skills while still injecting my posed style.
Sweet 11 day old Veer.  Didn’t even try to wake up the whole shoot.

My second of two newborn shoots today.  3 week old Everly arrived into the world 5 weeks early at just over 4 pounds.  She is small but she is mighty!  So glad we where able to make this session work before she and her family head back to Red Sucker Lake.
5 month old Roslyn is feeling the spring vibes, even if our weather hasn’t gotten the memo yet.
The sweet little newborn details.  The ones you never want to forget.
There is just something about maternity sessions that spark happiness in me.  I love when a woman chooses to celebrate and capture this time in their life.
Cheers to a safe, happy long weekend my friends :)

“What happens if my baby won’t sleep for the shoot?” I get this question a lot.  And the short answer is, I adjust.  Sometimes those alert images are even better (but harder to get). Don’t stress.  I have lots of tricks up my sleeve.
Dogs catching treats.  Need I say more :)
Someone was very proud to show off her baby sister today.
37 weeks and ready to hold her second baby any day now.
Ohhhhhh. Newborn side eye!!!!
Who else is this excited to finally have spring????

I first met Fievel almost 8 years ago when he was just a pup looking to be adopted.  Right after his adoption photo was taken his foster decided she just couldn’t let him go.  Oh and she was told he would be “medium size”. Just goes to show it’s always a guess with rescues.  He ended up being a pony.  I love catching up with my dogs :)
9 day old Morireoluwa came to see me today.  He slept through the whole visit.
What are the chances or two babies being this happy at the same time??? Like 0.1%? I’m so happy I got to catch up with these two.  I haven’t seen them since their newborn session a year ago.
16 day old Sirat.  She’s keeping my streak of amazing sleepers going strong.  And I thank her for that.
I truly consider what I do a privilege. The people I meet and capture all have a story.  Today it was five generations of women. From age 4 months to 88 years young.
How cute are these babies?  The bug litter will be looking for forever families soon.  Watch for them over at @mgprescue
Yes the gowns are amazing. But a simple piece of silk can be magical.  Lucky for my clients trust the process :)
There is just nothing like a sleepy, relaxed newborn.
What’s the only thing sweeter than a cake smash???? A twin cake smash of course.
My streak of sleepy happy babies continued today with 10 day old Skylar.  Even her big sister was pumped for photo day!
Harrison pretty much nailed his assignment today (and saved some for mom and dad).

When she arrived for her shoot today she proclaimed to be a tomboy and wanted super simple outfits.  Then I got her in this new gown and she transformed into the goddess she is.  Watching the confidence grow is my absolute favorite part of maternity shoots.
5 generations between these two lovely ladies.  If you needed something to make your smile, this is it.
Ready to meet baby any day now.
Dalton turned one today and spent the morning with me celebrating.  He didn’t eat much but he sure knows how to smash.
10 day old Harrison slept through his whole shoot.  He was just content to let me do my thing while I chatted with his parents.
Day one of mom and me minis done!  Thank you so much to all the families who came out today and kudos to the moms who got in front the the camera with their babies.

Today I had the honor of meeting 12 year old Onyx.  His family have had to make the hardest of decisions and will be saying goodbye.  His mom used to care for my boy Elroy years ago at doggy day care.  #projectgooddog was named after Elroy.  It was a bitter sweet full circle.
I can’t get enough of this little guy.
Tone on tone has to be one of my favorite looks in the studio.  And this color is perfection.

Yesterday Archie came into the studio on his first birthday for a photoshoot.  He was a little camera shy  but how can resist this face.  Fun fact: I am horribly allergic to cats.  So yes I do photograph them but I have to limit my exposure.
Mom and me studio minis part one.
Mom and me minis part two.
Yes Ava. Cake is this exciting!!!!
My second of two smash sessions today.  Miss Marie-Claire was an absolute sweet heart.
Miss Brielle was in the studio today to celebrate her upcoming birthday.  She had a blast, even in the tub.
Snuck in a couple more mom and me minis over the weekend.  Because moms need to be in front of the camera.

This beautiful mama requested I wait to share any images until baby arrived.  Well, baby is here and everyone is doing fantastic.  This image was created indoors, in the studio in terrible weather.  You would never know ;)

Contest time!!!!! I’m giving away a spring or summer 2023 outdoor mini session.  What’s a mini?  20 minute session with 10 retouched digital files. This is open to family (no extended family), kids, dogs, or maternity.  You know, the stuff I shoot.  Location will be south end Winnipeg and session will take place in the evening.  Okay, how to enter??? Like this post, make sure you follow @sunnyshphoto (I will check) and comment by tagging someone else you think would also like to win. Each comment is an entry.  Bonus?  Post in your stories too. Easy right?  Contest will close Friday May 12th evening.  Session must be used before Aug 31, 2023.  Session value is $325 plus taxes.  Enter as many times as you wish.  Happy tagging!
Wishing Liam the happiest of first birthdays in 2 days!!! So much fun catching up with him and his family this morning.
Those delicious newborn details.  The ones you want to remember forever.
Ahhhh. The weather is finally fitting for outdoor sessions.  Don’t want the weather stress and want to play in all the gowns?  No worries.  Studio sessions are year round.
Shawn was in the studio today to celebrate his upcoming birthday and he was PUMPED!!!
Carter just turned one!  Today we celebrated with cake and he did not hesitate.
Smile!!! It’s Friday!  16 day old Siming came to see me today and was all smiles.  Mostly cause of all the toots. But I’ll pretend it was my jokes.
First of two maternity sessions today.  I pushed her out of her comfort zone at the end with this ruffly number.  Honestly she made every gown look so good.
Every maternity session is catered to my clients comfort level and taste.  This stunning mama to be wanted to proudly show off that bump.  And she clearly rocked it.
I had the honor of meeting 17 year old Baby today.  Sadly his human has had to make the hardest of choices to say goodbye this week.  He’s been her “baby” his whole life.  #projectgooddog
Daniel came to visit me yesterday for his sitting stage milestone.  This will forever be my favorite baby stage.
Kyro just celebrated his first birthday.  Loving all these adorable baby milestones in the studio lately.
Newborn details.  All of those little things you never want to forget.
All the boho vibes today.  And the best part about my studio maternity sessions…central air!!!! On a day like today I’m so thankful for AC and chill clients.
Kids portraits don’t have to be 100% serious “smile at the camera”. Trust me. You will love seeing their personalities captured to look back on later.

I had the honor of meeting 15 year old Daisy tonight for a #projectgooddog session.  Her family knows their time left with her is short and wanted to make sure they had a beautiful portrait of her.  She made it very easy for me.
Fine art maternity sessions are quickly becoming a client favorite.  And this makes me so happy!!!! Celebrate this time in your life.  Capture it.  Let me show you just how gorgeous you are.
Link came to visit me today for his sitting stage milestone.  He was so excited for this stage he started practicing/sitting by 5 months old.
12 day old Éva was in the studio today and was an absolute doll for me.  We went with a “may flowers” vibe.

Today marks the last day of my 8 week shred/challenge.  This was my opportunity to peel back a few layers and see the hard work I’ve been putting in the last 2+ years.  My focus has been lifting heavy and doing cardio that I love.  I have also added in block therapy/yoga to keep my body happy and injury free.  This is days/weeks/months/years of consistency.  Do I do it to compete?  Nope.  I do this so may body can stay fit and injury free as I age.  If you know me I also am not the type who loves photos of myself. But I also want to celebrate and capture my achievements.  So I make myself get out of my comfort zone.  Am I done?  Nope.  Always room to improve. 📷 @rejeanbrandt  Posing/coaching: @jendalke
I am out of the office June 1-6th.  I’ll still have email/message access for bookings or questions  but galleries are on hold until I’m back.  Have a great week everyone.

Okay. Let’s talk AI.  It’s all the buzz and not going away anytime soon.  For me I think it’s a tool to help enhance portraits.  It won’t change how I shoot as I still need that image of the client just the way I want it but situations where I want to add elements it’s the perfect application.  In this case changing the backdrop to incorporate the colors and pampas my client adores.  I also send both versions to my client so she can choose what she loves.  What’s your take on AI?
11 day old Harrison came to visit me today.  His parents where worried he would not sleep for me.
Aria is turning three so it was time for our annual birthday session.  We where both so happy to just be outdoors and exploring.
Lux is turning one!!!! This little lady gave me all the faces today and smashed that cake so hard.  A perfect session in my books.

BIG NEWS!  I am extremely honored to finally share the announcement that myself and my golden girls are officially ambassadors for the @canadiananimalbloodbank along side @aceburpee @johnrush5 and @randyparkerr (incredible company to be in). What does this mean?  I’ll be sharing more content about animal blood donation and how donors can save lives.  We will also be attending events such as the golf tournament coming up July 6th where for the first time ever, dogs will be welcome on the course.  For a little background my girls have donated a total of 30 times now.  That alone has saved up to 90 other dogs.  Sophie is at 18 donations, Mindy (my rescue from @mgprescue ) is at 12.  Charlie is unable to donate due to medical reasons but she is part of the pack.  To be asked to represent an organization that means so much to me is humbling and I hope I can share awareness and information.  If you have any questions at all about whether your dog can donate, message me anytime.  The reality is most people don’t even know this need exists.  A big thank you to @sightlinesphoto for getting my first ever photo of me with my girls for this project.
Okay, who’s a Zelda fan?  Cause I’m pretty sure Link is :)
Sweet 10 day old Jack slept through his whole shoot today.
Emma - graduating class of 2023.  And yes I still have room for grad shoots this month :)
That time I did a cake smash for my baby girl.  Over the top?  Maybe… #noregrats
Janet came to visit me today for her 100 day session.  This is a very important milestone in Chinese culture and is often babies first photoshoot.
The only thing better than cake is sharing cake with your best friend.  Happy upcoming first birthday Marlowe.

When your client professes they are not “the frilly type” and then they do this…. Maternity is a time to celebrate, capture and remember. It’s my job to show each mom to be just how gorgeous they are. (New gown part of my studio closet).
Sweet and simple.  Jaxson came to see me yesterday to capture his sitting stage baby milestone.  Probably my favorite baby stage.

Dear grads of 2023.  You have weathered a crazy 3 years.  Online learning, constant change and so many lost  moments and milestones.  But you did it.  And you did it with grace.  We are all so proud of you.  Now go celebrate (safely) and make sure to capture these moments.
I suspect this newest gown for the client closet will become a favorite.  It’s 100% over the top glam.  Just how I want my expectant moms to feel.

Announcement!!! I am now offering in home lifestyle newborn/family sessions.  Yes, the studio poses sessions are still there too.  But this is a great option for those who aren’t into the props and want to focus on the bond with the families newest arrival.  For years I feel like my focus has been solely on the “perfect, controlled” sessions and I want to expand on capturing more of families stories.  Anywhooo.  What do you think?  I’m genuinely curious.
They say that humans start to look like their furry best friends.  Well I’d say they are twinning hard.
I’ve known this gorgeous young woman since she was born.  Tuesday she’s a high school grad and heading off to u of w in education.  Happy graduation Olivia.
Perfect smiles are amazing…but something about those faces kids make at a certain age that capture who they really are make my heart happy.  These are the ones parents will appreciate later.
